## Random Data Generators

```dart
class RandomDataGenerator {
  static final _random = Random();

  static String randomName() {
    const names = ['Max', 'Bella', 'Charlie', 'Luna', 'Cooper', 'Lucy', 'Buddy', 'Daisy', 'Rocky', 'Molly'];
    return names[_random.nextInt(names.length)];
  }

  static String randomBreed(String species) {
    if (species == 'Dog') {
      const breeds = ['Golden Retriever', 'Labrador', 'German Shepherd', 'Beagle', 'Poodle', 'Bulldog'];
      return breeds[_random.nextInt(breeds.length)];
    } else {
      const breeds = ['Persian', 'Maine Coon', 'Siamese', 'British Shorthair', 'Ragdoll', 'Bengal'];
      return breeds[_random.nextInt(breeds.length)];
    }
  }

  static String randomGender() {
    return _random.nextBool() ? 'Male' : 'Female';
  }

  static DateTime randomBirthday() {
    final daysAgo = _random.nextInt(3650); // 0-10 years
    return DateTime.now().subtract(Duration(days: daysAgo));
  }

  static String randomImageUrl(String species) {
    if (species == 'Dog') {
      return UnsplashImages.dogs[_random.nextInt(UnsplashImages.dogs.length)];
    } else {
      return UnsplashImages.cats[_random.nextInt(UnsplashImages.cats.length)];
    }
  }
}
```

## Usage in Repositories

```dart
// In PetRepository
Future<List<Pet>> getAllPets() async {
  final json = await _storage.getString(StorageKeys.pets);
  
  if (json == null || json.isEmpty) {
    // First time, return sample data
    final samplePets = MockDataService.getSamplePets();
    await _savePets(samplePets);
    return samplePets;
  }
  
  // Parse stored data
  final List<dynamic> decoded = jsonDecode(json);
  return decoded.map((item) => Pet.fromJson(item)).toList();
}

// In PostRepository
Future<List<Post>> getAllPosts() async {
  // Always return mock data (no persistence needed for demo)
  return MockDataService.getSamplePosts();
}
```

## Content Guidelines

### Post Content Examples
- Training tips and success stories
- Cute moments and funny behaviors
- Health and care advice
- Product recommendations
- Community questions and discussions

### Realistic Details
- Vary post timestamps (hours to weeks ago)
- Mix of high and low engagement (likes/comments)
- Diverse content types (educational, entertaining, emotional)
- Appropriate hashtags for filtering

### User Personas
1. **Trainer/Expert**: Educational content, professional advice
2. **Casual Owner**: Daily life, cute pics, questions
3. **Enthusiast**: Product reviews, lifestyle content
4. **Professional**: Veterinary advice, health tips

